The paper deals with object detection and classification within X-ray security imagery using Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs). This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and computer security and cryptography (cs.CR) categories. The paper also explores transfer learning and generalization of CNN models, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with the generation of adversarial datasets, which is a topic in multimedia (cs.MM).
